heisigComment: * As a primitive, this kanji will mean table.
heisigStory: This kanji depicts a pot of beans, although it looks more like a table on which the pot is resting.
koohiiStory1: If I eat BEANS, after ONE MOUTHful I fart like some kind of HORNED ANIMAL.
koohiiStory2: I hate using primitives that are completely unrelated. Let´s call this one Mr. Bean! He´s an easy character to build stories with.
readingExamples: 豆腐 (とうふ), 納豆 (なっとう), 豆 (まめ)
words: beans, peas, (as a prefix) miniature, tiny
